1-z^7
z = 1
z - e^{\frac 07} = z-1
 1 + z^2 + \ldots + z^6 = \frac {1-z^7}{1-z} 
 1-z^7 = 0 \\ z = \sqrt [7]1 = \sqrt[7]{e^{0\cdot pi}} = \{ e^{\frac {2\pi ki}7}\}, k = 0,1,\ldots,6 
 1-z^7 = \prod_{k = 0}^6 \left (z - e^{\frac {2\pi ki}7}\right) 
 \sum_{k=0}^6 z^k = \prod_{k=1}^6 \left(z-e^{\frac {2\pi ki}7} \right)  
 \sum_{k=0}^n z^k = \frac {1-z^{n+1}}{1-z} = \frac {\displaystyle \prod_{k = 0}^n \left(z-e^{\frac {2\pi ki} n} \right)}{1-z} = \prod_{k = 1}^n \left(z-e^{\frac {2\pi ki}n} \right) 
